        "body": "## Summary\n- add provider-shaped fake servers for Slack and WhatsApp alongside Telegram\n- share fake-server HTTP parsing/listen/response helpers across providers\n- wire Slack/WhatsApp through the fake-provider registry, CLI serve command, public exports, and OpenClaw adapter helpers\n- document the supported fake servers and native Slack/WhatsApp target identifiers\n\n## Details\n- Slack fake server implements auth.test, chat.postMessage, conversations.open, conversations.info, conversations.history, conversations.replies, plus admin inbound event injection.\n- WhatsApp fake server implements an OpenClaw active WhatsApp Web listener-shaped local API for message sends, presence sends, health checks, and admin inbound injection.\n- The OpenClaw adapter keeps Telegram compatibility and adds native-ID-only Slack and WhatsApp mappings.\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm verify",
